OL,3,GNEWSCBBC Scotland TV and radio
OL,4,Cprogrammes disrupted by fire
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe Scottish Fire and Rescue Service
OL,7,Fconfirmed that an air conditioning
OL,8,Fsystem located on the fifth floor of
OL,9,Fthe building had caught fire.
OL,11,FThe fire alarm took BBC Radio Scotland
OL,12,Foff air shortly after 6.30am. The
OL,13,Fstation was broadcasting a news
OL,14,Fbulletin when a report was faded out
OL,15,Fand replaced with music from an
OL,16,Femergency tape.
OL,18,FMusic and regular pre-recorded
OL,19,Fapologies were broadcast until 7am,
OL,20,Fwhen BBC Radio Scotland began
OL,21,Fsimulcasting BBC Radio 5 Live.
OL,23,Uppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
